comments.en: This is the Materials Design Ontology.

comment.en: A computational method is a way to process structures and/or properties into output structures and/or calculated properties.
A computational method parameter is one of the parameter settings of the method used for calculation.
HartreeFock method is a method to get the approximation of the determination of the wave functiona and the energy of system in a stationary state.
To represent an element in the periodic table.
A length triple consists of three bases of a unit cell.
An occupancy ties a specific species to a site.

seeAlso.value: International Tables for Crystallography, Volume A, Fourth, revised edition, Section 8.1.5.

comment.en: A group of linear mappings of vector space, which is corresonpond to the group of motions in point space determining the symmetry of the macroscopic crystal, is called the point group of the crystal, furthermore of the crystal structure, and is also called the point group of its space group.
A software agent is the representation of the software that produces the result of a material calculation.
A lattice is a set of points abstracted from basis.
A reference agent is the representation of the reference that the material data refers to.
Properties of structures or materials that are not influenced by calculations.
A basis can be described by basis's length vector a, b, c and the intervector angles alpha, beta and gamma.
A calculation is the use of a specific computational method to process structures and/or properties into output structures and/or calculated properties.
A site is a point in a lattice.
A composition is used to represent the composition of chemical elements of structures.
A coordinate vector is the coordinates of a point in space.
Properties of structures or materials that are influenced by calculations.
A structure is the information of the sites and their occupancies in a material or materials system.
A property in materials design is data pertaining to at least one material or materials system.

seeAlso.value: International Tables for Crystallography, Volume !, Fourth, revised edition, Section 8.1.5.

comment.en: A space group is the symmetry group of a three-dimensional crystal pattern is called its space group.
The density functional theory is a computational quantum mechanical modelling method to investigate the electronic structure.
A angle triple is a vector of three angles which represent the angles among three bases in a unit cell.
A species is the combination of atoms on each site.

seeAlso.value: An ExchangeCorrelationEnergyFunctional is the function to compute Exchange Correlation Energy.
